ðŸ”¹ awk (Pattern Scanning & Processing)
awk is a powerful programming language for text processing and data extraction, especially useful for column-based operations.

ðŸ› ï¸ Syntax:

        awk 'pattern { action }' file

ðŸ“Œ Common Uses:

        Print specific fields

        Perform calculations

        Filter data with conditions

ðŸ§ª Examples:

        awk '{print $1}' file.txt              # Print 1st column
        awk -F, '{print $2}' data.csv          # Use comma as delimiter
        awk '$3 > 50' data.txt                 # Print rows where 3rd field > 50
        awk '{sum += $2} END {print sum}' file.txt   # Sum 2nd column
